Package: anrepr
Type: Package
Title: Analysis Reporting in R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: as.person("Andrey Tovchigrechko <andreyto@gmail.com>[aut, cre]")
Description: A graphical loggin facility for saving dynamic and static plots, 
    tables and other analysis outputs from arbitrary locations inside your 
    analysis code and generating as your final output a static Web site with
    multiple pages containing auto-numbered and linked sections, plots and tables.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
    pander,
    stringr,
    methods
Suggests:
    testthat,
    roxygen2,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    ggplot2,
    DT,
    plotly,
    threejs
SystemRequirements: Pandoc should be present in the OS to generate HTML reports    
RoxygenNote: 7.0.2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
